    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently the virtual lines for Rust do not look great and the movement between lines causes eyesight to jump up or down a mostly blank line which is not ideal.\n\n<img width=\"493\" height=\"407\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2a7594df-8c38-4427-9f6d-bbf30a564c76\" />\n\nThe spacing issues looks like it is part of [this](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38676) issue, however it looks like it is closed unplanned.\n\nThe change occurred in the [0.12](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/36469) change I am not seeing any specific way to fix the spacing or revert the virtual positioning to the previous `0.11` version.\n\nI would consider the moving to a different default virtual position without a way to configure as a regression since it seems like the spacing is now off due to LSP configurations that are part of the \"unplanned\" work at the moment.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCan we add a configuration to be able to set the virtual position back to virtual text as it was in `0.11` so that we can fix the spacing in the meantime for LSPs and users decide wanting a virtual line for said text?",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I use the ccls language server for identifier references. My Emacs setup puts CodeLens at the end of the line in gray text, which looks great. (https://maskray.me/blog/2024-10-20-ccls-and-lsp-semantic-tokens)\n\n<img width=\"416\" height=\"493\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/fc71fb9f-2b5a-433b-934d-8468ba13a20d\" />\n\nThe current positioning in Neovim, however, is pretty distracting.\n\n<img width=\"541\" height=\"1275\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/76aacf70-005a-4d43-a888-5850b119aaf0\" />\n\n<details>\n<summary>C++ code</summary>\n\n```cpp\nenum E { X0, X1, X2, X3 };\nnamespace ns {\nusing Int = int;\nstruct B {\n  int x;\n};\ntemplate <class T>\nstruct D : B {\n  int y;\n  static long static_data;\n  void method0() {}\n  void method1() {}\n  static void static_method() {}\n};\n\nD<int> global_d;\ntemplate <> long D<int>::static_data = 1;\n\nstatic int static0 = 1, static1 = 1;\n}\n\nint foo(int p0, int p1, int p2) {\n  static int static_int = 1;\n  ns::Int v0=0, v1=1, v2=2, v3=3;\n  ns::D<int> d{};\n  d.x = d.x + ns::global_d.y + p0;\n  v0 = v0 * 2;\n\n  ns::D<int>::static_data ++;\n  d.method0();\n  d.method1();\n  d.static_method();\n  return ++static_int;\n}\n\nvoid foo1() {}\nvoid foo2() {}\nvoid foo3() {}\n```\n\n</details>\n\n",
