            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> My Emacs setup puts CodeLens at the end of the line in gray text, which looks great.\n\ngee, I wonder what could possibly go wrong with that.\n\nWe used to put diagnostics at EOL, and people didn't like that. One reason being, it is common for lines to be longer than the viewport.\n\n> Expected behavior: add a configuration to be able to set the virtual position\n\nAdding a random boolean flag isn't acceptable. But the door is open for more control over this, if we find a conventional way to provide it for most LSP features, instead of doing it in a bespoke way for each random feature.\n\nAnalogous to how `on_list` is a very generic way to override \"list\" behavior of `vim.lsp.buf.references()`, `vim.lsp.buf.implementation()`, etc. Also related: `vim.Scope` https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39570#discussion_r3207324542",
