            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> Adding a random boolean flag isn't acceptable. But the door is open for more control over this, if we find a conventional way to provide it for most LSP features, instead of doing it in a bespoke way for each random feature.\n\nI guess my confusion is that it seems the default was virtual text and then in the recent update it was changed to virtual line(s). I am curious what prompted the default change? If a boolean flag isn't acceptable, is there a way to opt out of the default somehow without having to move back to `0.11`?\n\nI agree that there is a gap here in the LSP features and that should be addressed but I also think we should have something in place for allowing previous support (unless it really is in conflict with some other feature that would be hard to untangle).",
