            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Another reason is that, by the combination of `vim.lsp.inlay_hint`, nvim now grants LSP servers the ability to show virtual text on any arbitrary positions in a buffer. If a server wants to show virtual text inline, use inlay hint; wants to show virtual text on a new line, use code lens.\n\nThis is also the reason to align code lenses with the position the LSP server provided, it's to give all the control to the servers.",
